data.name: btnRamp.ToolTip
data.value: Builds a sequential ramp of colors instead of random colors

data.name: cmdRefresh.ToolTip
data.value: Regenerates all the colors randomly, using the same original categories.

data.name: btnExclude.ToolTip
data.value: Design a filter expression so that only members not selected by this expression will be counted.

data.name: radUniqueValues.ToolTip
data.value: This option creates a separate value for each distinct member of the specified field.

data.name: radQuantities.ToolTip
data.value: This option uses mathematical criteria to group features into categories based on the value in the specified field.

data.name: btnAdd.ToolTip
data.value: Adds a new category to the set.

data.name: btnDelete.ToolTip
data.value: Removes the selected category from the set.

data.name: btnUp.ToolTip
data.value: Moves the selected category up in the list.

data.name: btnDown.ToolTip
data.value: Lowers the selected category in the list.

data.name: cmbNormField.ToolTip
data.value: Instead of grouping based on the actual value in a field, this allows you to specify a divisor so that the ratio is categorized instead.

data.name: nudSigFig.ToolTip
data.value: Significant figures represent the number of digits in a decimal value that contain meaningful values, and that number of digits will be displayed.

data.name: cmbIntervalSnapping.ToolTip
data.value: Controls whether precise numbers with lots of digits are used, or numbers that have fewer non-zero values and are therfore easier to read.

data.name: dgvStatistics.ToolTip
data.value: Describes the summary statistics for the values in the field. This may only be a representative sample.
